SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION—Urging Congress to protect the
public lands including and adjacent to Sunrise Mountain,
Frenchman Mountain and the Rainbow Gardens Area.
1 WHEREAS, The public lands including and adjacent to Sunrise
2 Mountain, Frenchman Mountain and the Rainbow Gardens Area are
3 undeveloped natural treasures located near the Las Vegas Valley;
4 and
5 WHEREAS, These public lands contain colorful mountain ranges
6 rising up from the desert lowlands; and
7 WHEREAS, Gypsum Cave, which holds some of the earliest
8 evidence of human inhabitance in the western United States and is
9 significant to Indian tribes, is located on these public lands; and
10 WHEREAS, These public lands contain evidence of the Great
11 Unconformity, which consists of exposed surface rock that
12 represents more than one quarter of the history (1.2 billion years) of
13 the Earth’s crust and tectonic plates; and
14 WHEREAS, Several plant species that have received special
15 status designation by the Bureau of Land Management are found on
16 these public lands; and
-
