1 WHEREAS, Many Nevada residents enjoy the natural desert
2 landscape and the outdoor recreational opportunities of Sunrise
3 Mountain, Frenchman Mountain and the Rainbow Gardens Area;
4 now, therefore, be it
5 RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF
6 NEVADA, JOINTLY, That the members of the 83rd Session of the
7 Nevada Legislature hereby urge Congress to protect the public lands
8 including and adjacent to Sunrise Mountain, Frenchman Mountain
9 and the Rainbow Gardens Area by designating them for federal
10 protection, which may include, without limitation, designating all or
11 portions of the area as a national conservation area, national
12 recreation area or national monument, or applying other federal
13 protections that Congress deems appropriate for these important and
14 scenic lands; and be it further
15 RESOLVED, That the Secretary of the Senate prepare and
16 transmit a copy of this resolution to the Vice President of the United
17 States as the presiding officer of the Senate, the Speaker of the
18 House of Representatives and each member of the Nevada
19 Congressional Delegation; and be it further
20 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
21 passage.
